2.00	Transportation_in_the_Democratic_Republic_of_the_Congo	Transport in the Democratic Republic of the Congo	Ground transport in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) has always been difficult. The terrain and climate of the Congo Basin present serious barriers to road and rail construction, and the distances are enormous across this vast country. Furthermore, chronic economic mismanagement and internal conflict has led to serious under-investment over many years.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7f/Congo_Transport_Map.PNG/300px-Congo_Transport_Map.PNG
